Project Title

FocusQuest: Gamified Productivity Tracker for Students
SDG Chosen - SDG 4: Quality Education
Problem Statement
Many students struggle to stay focused while studying due to distractions such as social media (YouTube, X). This leads to reduced productivity and poor learning outcomes.
Solution

FocusQuest is a gamified productivity application that:
- Rewards students with XP when they focus on productive websites
- Penalizes distractions through gameplay mechanics
- Encourages consistent study habits using character progression

Target Users
- High school students
- University students
- Self-learners

 Key Features

1.	Focus Tracking System
a) Detects productive websites
b) Rewards XP based on time spent

2.	Distraction Penalty System
a) Detects time spent on distracting sites
b) Applies penalties (sleep state, XP reduction)
 
3.	Character Progression
a) Level system
b) Health/Mana bars
c) Rest mechanic

Value Proposition
FocusQuest transforms studying into an engaging experience by combining productivity tracking with game elements, helping students stay focused and improve learning efficiency

